&lt;p&gt;Job Title: Senior Software Engineer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: 10770 NE 8th Street, Suite 700, Bellevue, WA 98004&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;*Telecommuting permitted: work may be performed within normal commuting distance from The Trade Desk office in Bellevue, WA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Duties: Design and implement scalable software components and infrastructure within internal developer platforms and distributed systems to enhance engineering productivity and reliability. Optimize and refactor existing tooling, services, and workflows to reduce developer friction and improve system performance, fault tolerance, and maintainability across engineering teams. Conduct comprehensive technical design and code reviews for high-impact systems, ensuring architectural alignment, adherence to secure coding practices, and performance efficiency. Serve as a technical advisor to guide software design patterns and best practices across teams. Lead cross-functional technical initiatives by scoping and executing complex projects that span multiple services, teams, and domains, including dependency resolution, phased rollouts, and backward compatibility. Develop reusable frameworks and internal APIs to enable standardized integration and extensibility across the company’s engineering organization; own shared libraries or SDKs used by multiple services and teams. Use telemetry, logs, and operational data to identify bottlenecks, quantify the impact of engineering investments, and drive decisions around prioritization and architectural improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: $212,202 - $274,700 / year&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Requirements: Master&#39;s degree (U.S. or foreign equivalent) in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or related field and five (5) years of experience in the job offered or related role OR Bachelor’s degree (U.S. or foreign equivalent) in Computer Science, Computer Engineering, or related field and seven (7) years of experience in the job offered or related role. Must have five (5) year of experience with: REST APIs or gRPC; and Java, C#, or C++. Must have four (4) year of experience with: Microsoft SQL Server or MySQL; Grafana and Prometheus; AWS, including SQS, EC2, CloudTrail, IAM, AWS Autoscaling, CloudWatch, ECS and EKS; Kubernetes and Docker Container; and S3 or Azure Blob Storage.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CO, CA, IL, NY, WA, and Washington DC residents only:&lt;/strong&gt; In accordance with CO, CA, IL, NY, WA, and Washington DC law, the range provided is The Trade Desk&#39;s reasonable estimate of the base compensation for this role. The actual amount may differ based on non-discriminatory factors such as experience, knowledge, skills, abilities, and location. All employees may be eligible to become The Trade Desk shareholders through eligibility for stock-based compensation grants, which are awarded to employees based on company and individual performance. The Trade Desk also offers other compensation depending on the role such as sales-based incentives and commissions. Plus, expected benefits for this role include comprehensive healthcare (medical, dental, and vision) with premiums paid in full for employees and dependents, retirement benefits such as a 401k plan and company match, short and long-term disability coverage, basic life insurance, well-being benefits, reimbursement for certain tuition expenses, parental leave, sick time of 1 hour per 30 hours worked, vacation time for full-time employees up to 120 hours thru the first year and 160 hours thereafter, and around 13 paid holidays per year. &amp;nbsp;Employees can also purchase The Trade Desk stock at a discount through The Trade Desk’s Employee Stock Purchase Plan.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trade Desk also offers a competitive benefits package. Click &lt;a href=&quot;https://careers.thetradedesk.com/us/en&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to learn more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt; Interns are not eligible for variable incentive awards such as stock-based compensation, retirement plan, vacation, tuition reimbursement or parental leave&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;At the Trade Desk, Base Salary is one part of our competitive total compensation and benefits package and is determined using a salary range. The base salary range for this role is &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$212,202&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$274,700 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Equal Opportunity Employer, The Trade Desk is committed to creating an inclusive hiring experience where everyone has the opportunity to thrive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please reach out to us at&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:accommodations@thetradedesk.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;accommodations@​thetradedesk.​com&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;to request an accommodation or discuss any accessibility needs you may require to access our Company Website or navigate any part of the hiring process.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you contact us, please include your preferred contact details and specify the nature of your accommodation request or questions. Any information you share will be handled confidentially and will not impact our hiring decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
